      "title" : "The day you let your queue spin the globe (and then some)",
      "description" : "From late-night grime and bossa nova to jazz house, retro soul, and a midday salsa detour, your queue never lingered in one place for long. By afternoon, “Chorar Na Beira Do Mar” and “Colors” kept returning, while Discover Weekly served up a world tour of sounds. 333 minutes, 104 tracks, 79 artists—your most diverse day of the year.",
